Flutter Intern -
1. Building and shipping robust apps to Android/ iOS devices using a single
codebase (Flutter).
2. Writing readable and clear code using Dart that will be extensively
documented for future use and upgrades.
3. Sharing feedback and brainstorming ideas with teams to improve the
development process.
4. Understanding basic concepts of design for developing user-friendly
applications.
5. Staying up to date with the latest technologies.

Skills and qualifications:

1. Experience in the development of Android/iOS applications using Flutter
and have deployed them on Google Play/App Store.
2. Knowledge of mobile app development.
3. In-depth understanding of Flutter, BLOC
architecture/GetX/Provider/Riverpod.
4. In-depth understanding of Object Oriented programming languages like
Dart.
5. Familiarity using version control tools like Git, Subversion etc. and
IDEs like Android Studio, VS Code etc.
6. Understanding of the Agile Software Development Life Cycle and being
exposed to Scrum projects.
7. Knowledge of Dart programming language, Rest APIs and integration of
various APIs from third parties.
8. Comfortable using test cases for debugging code, enhancing performance
and reliability.

If you know someone talented who might be a good fit, refer them
to us.
